pageContext.claim: “And [Japan is] building many car plants here. Germany is doing the same thing. Germany has to do what they're doing, you know, building [automobile] plants.”
pageContext.analysis: Long before Trump became president, BMW began manufacturing in South Carolina, Daimler in Alabama and Volkswagen in Tennessee. No new German plants have been added since he became president. (Toyota and Mazda have announced that they'll invest $1.6 billion and construct a new factory in Alabama.)
